# Major Formulas used to create table
## For Opportunity Score
Opportunity Score = w1(Demand) + w2(EconomicAttractiveness) - w3(Competition) 
# w1=w2=0.4, w3=0.2

# Demand proxy = restaurant/10k populatio
# Economic singal = median household income
# Competition = average restaurant rating

## For Value Score
Value Score = Rating-Price+Rent 
# some of the restaurants were missing price info. I didn't correct/impute them. 

## For weighted rating
$$
\text{WR} = \frac{v}{v + C} \cdot R + \frac{C}{v + C} \cdot m
$$

Where:  

- \(R\) = restaurant's raw rating  
- \(v\) = number of reviews for the restaurant  
- \(m\) = global mean rating (average across all restaurants)  
- \(C\) = smoothing constant (e.g., typical review count for credibility)


